<example xml:id="eg_basis_discrete">
  <statement>
    <p>
      Let <m>X</m> be a set, and let <m>\mathcal{T}</m> be the discrete topology on <m>X</m>. Show the following:
      <ol>
        <li>
          <p>
            <m>\mathcal{B}=\{ \{x\}\colon x\in X\}</m> is a basis for <m>\mathcal{T}</m>.
          </p>
        </li>
        <li>
          <p>
            If <m>\mathcal{B}'</m> is a basis for <m>\mathcal{T}</m>, then <m>\mathcal{B}\subseteq \mathcal{B}'</m>. In other words, <m>\mathcal{B}</m> is the minimal basis of the discrete topology.
          </p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </p>
